Hamas Fighter Blew Himself Up In Daring Attack On Israeli Army Post In Gaza (Videos)
A group of Hamas fighters attempted to raid an Israel Defense Forces (IDF) post near the city of Khan Younis in the southern Gaza Strip on August 20 morning, with one of the fighters blowing himself up and others attempting to kidnap Israeli troops.
According to an IDF probe, the attack began at around 9 a.m. local time, with at least 14 fighters emerging from a tunnel south of Khan Younis and opening fire with machine guns and rocket-propelled grenades while approaching the post. The probe acknowledged that some of the fighters managed to breach the post, which was manned by troops from the IDF‚Äôs Kfir Brigade. It assessed that the fighters sought to kidnap troops.

Russia‚Äôs Most Armed Nuclear Battlecruiser Takes To Waters On Trails (Video)
The heavy nuclear-powered nuclear-powered battlecruiser Admiral Nakhimov has taken to waters for trials after repairs and a major upgrade, a source in the domestic shipbuilding industry told TASS on August 18.
Admiral Nakhimov has been under repairs since 1999. Real work on the battlecruiser, including the integration of new weapon systems, has been carried out since 2013. Earlier in the year, the 28,000-ton warship‚Äôs two nuclear reactors went back online.
Admiral Nakhimov‚Äôs upgrade is centered around a plan to install 174 vertical launch cells, which would provide it with more than any other warship or submarine in the world.
